data.text:
Susan Saint James, center, mother of Teddy Ebersol, who died in a 2004 plane crash when he was 14 years-old, dries her eyes during a ceremony in Boston, Saturday, June 10, 2006 to dedicate new athletic fields on the Charles River as Teddy Ebersol's Red Sox Fields. Also seen, are her husband, NBC sports executive Dick Ebersol, left, and Sen. Edward Kennedy, D-Mass., right. (AP Photo/Josh Reynolds)
